{{Infobox person | name = Beverly 'Bevy' Smith | image = File:Bevy Smith.jpeg | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1966|11|02}} | birth_place = [[Harlem]], [[New York (state)|New York]], U.S. | occupation = Television host, business-woman | known_for = ''[[Fashion Queens]]'' | website = {{url|www.bevysmith.com}} }} '''Beverly 'Bevy' Smith''' (born November 2, 1966)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mediabistro.com/articles/details.asp?aID=12112& |title=SO WHAT DO YOU DO, BEVY SMITH, HOST OF BRAVO'S FASHION QUEENS? |publisher=Mediabistro |date=June 4, 2014 |first=Janelle |last=Harris |accessdate=October 15, 2014 }}</ref> is an American television personality and business woman. She is best known for her work as a co-host on [[Bravo (U.S. TV channel)|Bravo]]'s [[fashion]]-themed [[talk show]] ''[[Fashion Queens]]''.<ref>{{cite web|last=Wills|first=Cortney|title=Bevy Smith Talks Natural Hair, Miley Cyrus, Rihanna & ‘Fashion Queens’|url=http://cocoafab.com/exclusive-bevy-smith-talks-natural-hair-miley-cyrus-rihanna-fashion-queens/|work=CocoaFab|accessdate=January 22, 2014|date=November 4, 2013}}</ref> Smith is the creator of "Dinner with Bevy," a dinner party series in which she brings together people from across entertainment, fashion and media.<ref>{{cite web|last=Wilson|first=Julee|title=Bevy Smith's 'Dining With Bevy: Life With Vision' Series Grooms Next Generation Of Movers And Shakers|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/07/02/bevy-smith-dining-with-bevy-life-with-vision_n_1645654.html|work=The Huffington Post|accessdate=January 21, 2014|date=July 3, 2012}}</ref>
==Life and career== Bevy Smith was born, raised, and still resides in [[Harlem]], [[New York (state)|New York]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Warren|first=Tamara|title=Range Rover City Shapers: Bevy Smith Takes Manhattan|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/tamarawarren/2011/03/10/range-rover-city-shapers-bevy-smith-takes-manhattan/|work=Forbes|accessdate=January 21, 2014|date=March 20, 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Abadsidis|first=Savas|title=Bevy Smith, Bravo's Queen of Fashion|url=http://www.advocate.com/arts-entertainment/television/2013/12/22/bevy-smith-bravos-queen-fashion|work=The Advocate|publisher=Here Media Inc|accessdate=January 21, 2014|date=December 22, 2013}}</ref> Smith would later become the senior director of luxury fashion advertising at ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' and fashion and beauty advertising director for ''[[Vibe (magazine)|Vibe]]'' magazine.<ref>{{cite web|last=Phanor-Faury|first=Alexandra|title=Closet Envy: Fashion Insider Beverly Smith|url=http://www.essence.com/2010/05/19/closet-envy-beverly-smith/|work=Essence|accessdate=January 21, 2014|date=April 20, 2010}}</ref> Smith had been cast in ''[[Tim Gunn's Guide to Style]]'' but ended up passing on the opportunity.<ref name=pastjobs>{{cite web|last=Daniels|first=Karu|title=‘Fashion Queen’ Bevy Smith [INTERVIEW]|url=http://www.ebony.com/entertainment-culture/fashion-queen-bevy-smith-interview-999|work=EBONY Magazine|accessdate=January 21, 2014|date=November 5, 2013}}</ref> She also had a planned series on [[Oxygen (TV channel)|Oxygen]], titled Bevy: Queen of Shops, but she also passed on that offer. Bevy later accepted a job at [[BET]] prior to her becoming a co-host on ''Fashion Queens''.<ref name=pastjobs/>
On February 18, 2012, as a [[BET]] News correspondent, Smith hosted ''BET Remembers [[Whitney Houston]]''. The live special featured Smith as she interviewed several friends of Houston to share memories.<ref>{{cite web|title=BET News and CENTRIC to Broadcast Live Coverage of Whitney Houston's Funeral Services This Saturday, February 18 Beginning at 11:30AM ET, Followed by a One Hour Original Special "BET REMEMBERS WHITNEY" at 7:00PM*|url=http://ir.viacom.com/releasedetail.cfm?ReleaseID=649501|publisher=Viacom|accessdate=January 21, 2014|date=February 16, 2012}}</ref> In February and September 2012, Smith appeared as a guest on the [[VH1]] talk show, ''[[Big Morning Buzz Live]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=''Big Morning Buzz Live'': Ep. 322|url=http://www.vh1.com/shows/big_morning_buzz_live/episode.jhtml?episodeID=189753|work=VH1|accessdate=January 21, 2014}}</ref> In December 2012, Smith appeared on Bravo's ''Watch What Happens Live'' with [[Jenna Jameson]] and [[Jennifer Tilly]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Jenna Jameson, Bevy Smith & Jennifer Tilly|url=http://www.bravotv.com/watch-what-happens-live/season-10/photos/jenna-jameson-bevy-smith-jennifer-tilly|work=Bravo|accessdate=January 21, 2014}}</ref> Smith has made several appearances on the talk show, ''[[Bethenny (TV series)|Bethenny]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=Bevy Smith: Credits|url=http://www.tvguide.com/celebrities/bevy-smith/credits/363077|work=TV Guide|accessdate=January 21, 2014}}</ref> On June 3, 2014, Smith appeared as guest co-host on the talk show, ''[[The View (U.S. TV series)|The View]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title= Scoop: THE VIEW - Week of 6/2 on ABC|url= http://www.broadwayworld.com/bwwtv/article/Scoop-THE-VIEW-Week-of-62-on-ABC-20140529#.U43oYC9RHbE|work=BroadwayWorld|accessdate=June 3, 2014}}</ref>
Since 2015, she has been hosting a daily, one hour radio show on SiriusXM's RadioAndy called ''Bevelations''. She also appears on BET's ''[[Wendy's Style Squad]],'' where she recaps award show fashion with Wendy Williams and other co-hosts.
Since 2017, she has co-hosted the entertainment news show Page Six TV. Page Six TV is the television version of the well known Page Six section of The New York Post.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://pagesix.com/tv/about/|title=About Page Six TV|website=pagesix.com|language=en|access-date=2018-02-21}}</ref>
